videos.description: Esa Ahmad steals the ball from Baylor and West Virginia gets it to Teyvon Myers, who sinks the bucket and draws the foul.
videos.headline: WVU getting it done on defense and offense

videos.description: West Virginia moving the ball around, Teyvon Myers passes to Brandon Watkins, who finishes with the dunk.
videos.headline: Watkins slams it down for West Virginia

videos.description: West Virginia's Jevon Carter gets the rebound and takes it to the other end for a lay-up
videos.headline: Jevon Carter scores after going coast-to-coast

videos.description: Nathan Adrian gets the ball and hits a jumper to give West Virginia a 39-32 lead over Baylor at the half.
videos.headline: Adrian's jumper extends WVU's lead

videos.description: West Virginia's Esa Ahmad gets a steal and ends up with a basket at the other end to put West Virginia up 50-37.
videos.headline: West Virginia capitalizes on Baylor turnover with another score

videos.description: West Virginia's Tarik Phillip forces a Baylor turnover and finds Brandon Watkins open for a dunk.
videos.headline: Brandon Watkins throws down a two-handed dunk for WVU

videos.description: West Virginia's Daxter Miles Jr. finishes a putback dunk in response to a Nathan Adrian 3-Pointer from the previous possession.
videos.headline: Daxter Miles Jr. slams a putback dunk for WVU in win over No. 1 Baylor

videos.description: West Virginia's Sagaba Konate gets the block on Johnathan Motley and Jevon Carter makes a jumper at the other end to put West Virginia ahead 76-50.
videos.headline: WVU block leads to a jumper and a 26-point lead over Baylor

videos.description: West Virginia head coach Bob Huggins discusses what the 89-68 victory over Baylor means for the program.
videos.headline: Bob Huggins on his team's victory over Baylor and the performance of Nathan Adrian

videos.description: West Virginia forward Nathan Adrian on his team's gameplan in their 89-68 victory over Baylor.
videos.headline: Nathan Adrian describes what it took to get the win over Baylor

videos.description: West Virginia's fans join the team on the court to celebrate the Mountaineers' win over No. 1 Baylor.
videos.headline: West Virginia fans storm the court following win over Baylor

videos.description: Seth Greenberg says West Virginia's "suffocating" defense is so unique that even the No. 1 team in the nation couldn't prepare for it.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCB Analysis (Why West Virginia is a matchup nightmare) 2017/01/10 SC

videos.headline: Why West Virginia is a matchup nightmare
